==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mobocracy
<hw>Mob*oc"ra*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mob</ets>
rabble + <ets>-cracy</ets>, as in <ets>democracy</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
condition in which the lower classes of a nation control public affairs
without respect to law, precedents, or vested rights.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is good name that Dr. Stevens has given to our present
situation (for one can not call it a government), a
<qex>mobocracy</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mobocrat</ent>⟦br⟧
